Supported Browsers and Devices for Lightning Experience
Supported Browsers and Devices for Salesforce Classic
Supported Browsers for CRM Analytics

Lightning Experience is available in Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions. When accessing Lightning Experience on a mobile device, we recommend that you use the Salesforce mobile app.

Consider these browser restrictions when working with Lightning Experience:
Salesforce doesn’t support nonbrowser applications that embed WebView or similar controls to render content for Lightning Experience.
Lightning Experience doesn’t support incognito or other private browsing modes.

Desktop and Laptop Browsers
Microsoft INTERNET EXPLORER Not supported
Microsoft EDGE (NON-CHROMIUM) Not supported
Microsoft EDGE CHROMIUM Supports latest stable browser version
GOOGLE CHROME Supports latest stable browser version
MOZILLA FIREFOX Supports latest stable browser version
APPLE SAFARI Supports latest stable browser version

Tablet Browsers
APPLE SAFARI on iPadOS Supported (use landscape orientation)
GOOGLE CHROME Not supported
OTHER BROWSERS Not supported
SALESFORCE MOBILE APP Supported

Phones
For the best experience, use the Salesforce mobile app.

Third-Party Browser Extensions and JavaScript Libraries
We recommend that you check AppExchange for browser extensions and apps from Salesforce partners or the Component Reference for base components that match your requirements.
title: Supported Browsers and Devices for Lightning Experience
